# Task

For each email, classify into exactly ONE of:
- `linkedin_alert` - LinkedIn job match notifications (e.g., "20 new jobs for your search")
- `job_alert` - Any other automated job-alert digest (Indeed, ZipRecruiter, Glassdoor, Built In, Wellfound, etc). Pick this when the email is a scheduled list of new job postings from a job board, not a human outreach.
- `recruiter` - Outreach from a recruiter or hiring manager (new opportunity, asking for time, following up)
- `app_update` - Update on an application the candidate submitted (received, in review, interview scheduled, screening, etc.)
- `rejection` - Application rejection or "decided to move forward with other candidates"
- `offer` - Job offer or offer-related discussion (compensation, negotiation)
- `other` - Anything else (promotions, newsletters, personal, spam)

# Output Format

Respond with ONLY a JSON array, one object per input email in the same order:

[
  {"index": 1, "category": "linkedin_alert"},
  {"index": 2, "category": "recruiter"},
  ...
]

No prose, no markdown fences. Just the JSON array.
